parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Fuel System Failure and Engine Compartment Heat Issues
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel system and excessive heat in the engine compartment can cause fuel leaks, fires, and burns to the rider, which can lead to accidents, injuries, and fatalities.
symptoms: Fuel fumes or strong fuel smell
fuel boiling in the tank
fuel dripping or leaking
extreme heat felt from under the seat area
burns to the inner thigh and knee areas
engine overheating
and engine failure.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Failure and Limp Home Mode
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine failure and limp home mode can cause loss of power, accidents, and injuries, especially when riding on highways.
symptoms: Engine failure
limp home mode
loss of power
engine light on
and inability to accelerate.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The vehicle can shift into reverse gear without warning, while driving at any speed, which can cause accidents, loss of control, or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle shifts into reverse gear independently
without warning
while driving downhill or on an incline
or at random times.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the engine oil flow regulator can cause engine damage, oil leaks, and potentially lead to engine failure, which can cause accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: A small screw or bolt is found inside the oil pan magnet
which regulates the amount of oil flow into the rear cylinder head; engine may still operate correctly
but may eventually start leaking oil along one of the cylinder head gaskets.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the evaporative emission control system can cause gasoline fumes to be emitted from the vent hose, which can lead to a fire hazard, especially in hot weather conditions.
symptoms: Gasoline fumes are emitted from the vent hose
especially when the bike is shut down
noticeable even when sitting still at a stop light or stuck in traffic
fumes often condense around the bottom lip of the vent hose
and the condensate collects around the lip and eventually drips off.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel system can cause fuel leaks, which can lead to a fire hazard, and in extreme cases, a vehicle fire.
symptoms: Fuel leaking from the fuel canister
strong gasoline odor
heat rising from beneath the vehicle
flames coming from the engine area.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Fuel Vapor Canister Failure and Gasoline Fumes
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel vapor canister can cause gasoline fumes to vent into the engine compartment and driver's area, leading to burning eyes, chest pains, and a potential fire or explosion hazard.
symptoms: Strong gasoline odor
fuel fumes venting into the engine compartment
fuel fumes venting into the driver's area
burning eyes
chest pains
irritation to the eyes and respiratory system.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine fire can cause damage to the vehicle and potentially lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Flames appear under the motorcycle near the engine area
strong fuel fumes around the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The fuel system failure can cause the vehicle to fail to start, and strong fuel fumes can lead to a fire hazard.
symptoms: Strong fuel fumes around the vehicle
vehicle fails to start
ABS and EBD default warnings displayed on the message board.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The turn signal switch failure can cause confusion and miscommunication with other drivers, leading to potential accidents.
symptoms: The turn signal switch jumps to the opposite direction when canceled
turn signal indicator lights are difficult to see in certain light conditions
the signal remains on for an extended period or does not turn off at all.
